text:
A Teaching Routine

1) Give students an old problem I wrote
2) Watch them struggle to make sense of it
3) Think "I should rewrite this later to make it clearer"
4) Later realize the struggle was exactly what I wanted
5) Leave the problem exactly as is

#math #mathchat #edchat

text:
@pwharris #mathstratchat  We used an "Over, Over" strategy.
as 7.8 = 8 - 0.2 and 45.9 = 46-0.1
so 7.8 + 45.9
= 8.0 - 0.2 + 46.0 - 0.1
= 8.0 + 46.0 - 0.3
= 54.0 - 0.3
= 53.7
Play with it here🧡: https://t.co/TVJvrS7h7A
